{
  "texts": [
    "Body information is stored using SMPL (Loper et al. 2015), which describes joint positions and surfaces.",
    "This allows the usage of several possible reconstruction losses: constraining part rotations in the kinematic tree, joint locations, or surface points.",
    "Positional encoding (Mildenhall et al. 2020) is a promising idea, but prior to this method, it was not used in motion planning.",
    "The relatively small number of motion capture (MoCap) datasets is a limitation for the 3D domain, which is why the authors opted to use monocular motion estimation methods (Kocabas et al. 2020).",
    "Fortunately, this choice makes it possible to learn larger-scale applications, since the data require less memory for training."
  ]
}